The Blade battery cell allows a greater cell-to-pack ratio as the cells can slip into the pack (no need for modules) and the advantages include an increase in the energy density of the pack and reduce need of supplementary materials (such as adhesives) [1]. Additionally, the blade cell are relatively low cost ($100/kWh) andthe large surface area allow substantial heat dissipation to reduce risk of thermal runaway. Furthermore, the design of the blades allows the employment of disassembly tabs to allow greater recoverability of cell material and ease of recycling [2].
